<br>
I'm going to take these as carefully as I can to avoid appearing confrontational.  My intention is NOT in any way to demean or diminish the opinion of PO or any of my fellow board members.  Rather, It is with the goal of clarifying PO's meanings and expressing my own opinions that I rewrite my post.<br>
<br>
1st off:<br>
I dont think Yales should be removed as a moderator.<br>
<br>
Why:<br>
I dont think the 'impression' that newcomers get is relevant.  Yales has opinions (and facts to back them up) that are just as valid and supportable as anything else out there.  In the spirit of a good debate, its necessary to have opposing viewpoints to be heard.<br>
I dont think anyone with a modicum of intelligence or experience posting on forums would be 'confused' by yales.  Your reference, as well, to 'speaking on behalf of the board'  is confusing to me.  I dont think anyone who visits forums expects the board to have an opinion.  Intelligent people are perfectly capable of forming their own opinions and arguing with information they find misleading.  I would never take a post by You, Zaph, Yales, NukeConsp. or B(does he exist?) as Nuclear Gospel, and I dont think anyone with critical thinking skills would either.  Those who would frequent the board who are sheepy enough to take someone elses opinion (regardless of whose it is) and make it their own without supporting evidence are useless to anyone in a debate or in resolving any issues and justly deserve to be ignored.  <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  It's rather embarassing when he gets to visitors first.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Embarrassing for who? Is it embarrassing to have to apologize for yales' opinions?  My response can only be: Dont apologize for them.  Respond to them with evidence.  <br>
A view from a relative newbie:<br>
<br>
It was clear when I arrived that the majority of this board was Pro-Nuclear and Pro-Space and I was Psyched!  I've been interested both in nuclear power and spaceflight for as long as I can remember having opinions.  I came to this board and I immediately felt at home (maybe a little more abusive than my home.. but whatever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).  I did not find Yales confusing or embarassing.  Its to be expected that there are people out there who will point out contradictions or difficulties with any goal.  I took it that Yales was the devils advocate.  Almost always necessary, even when what they say is infuriating and/or disagreeable.<br>
<br>
Most of this is irrelevant to his moderator status.  The issues I've seen arise (few as they are) seem to involve a few components.  I will try to walk through the 'flamewars' as I see them.  (These flamewars, by the way, are NOTHING compared to what I've seen on other boards.  ya'll are lucky to live in such a sheltered community that a disagreement becomes a flame in less than 4 or 5 posts.  Its impressive actually).<br>
note that the research for this format is taken from the threads here:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm15.showMessage?topicID=72.topic">pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclea...D=72.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm15.showMessage?topicID=70.topic">pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclea...D=70.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm15.showMessage?topicID=74.topic">pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclea...D=74.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
1:<br>
A statment is made<br>
2:<br>
Yales disagrees and demands to see proof<br>
3:<br>
The proof is generally unavailable (or VERY difficult to obtain)<br>
4:<br>
Yales takes it as victory<br>
5:<br>
Others do not take it as victory<br>
6:<br>
Arguments from past disagreements show up.<br>
7:<br>
thread dissolves into mish-mash and is moved.<br>
<br>
There seem to be very few ways to avoid the cycle.  Those that I see are:<br>
1) Dont say anything yales will disagree with<br>
(hardly an option)<br>
2) Make sure before you say anything that you have evidence to back it up.<br>
(this seems most reasonable)<br>
3) Let Yales &quot;win&quot; when you cannot back up arguments with evidence.  Just move on the the next topic and make sure you have evidence next time.<br>
(also not unreasonable, for mature posters)<br>
4) Get a thicker skin and dont take posts personally.  Wait 10 minutes before replying to any thread that angers you.<br>
(This applies both to yales and others.  Its good practice regardless.)<br>
<br>
I think that I have been fair to all parties and expressed myself clearly and (not very)concisely.<br>
Thanks.<br>
<br>
-Stilgar. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stilgar>Stilgar</A> at: 8/31/02 9:11:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1994<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/31/02 8:27:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Should Yales be removed as Moderator?</span><hr size=1> I was willing to give Yales the benefit of the doubt when he was given mod status. I had previously voiced my reservations at the suggestion category but I was also interested in seeing how the experiment turned out. Within days he posted a very long unprovoked flame against me. Yesterday he repeated this act. I find this intolerable from a high status member who should be setting an example to others. The person who is responsible for preventing flamestorms should not be starting them. He is an intelligent poster who is very informed on nuclear space issues but I am not happy with his overall behavior. I detect an impatience with newcomers which I think is damaging to this board. His penchant for swamping them with extremely long posts in an effort to impress only drives away curious visitors who think we are all rocket scientists and nuclear physicists. What else are they to think when they see a moderator preaching it to them.<br>
<br>
Finally ofcourse there is his opposition to the movement which simply doesn't sit well with me. It might have been less of a problem if Yales didn't keep putting across the myth he was speaking on behalf of the board. It's rather embarassing when he gets to visitors first. Probably confusing for them aswell.<br>
<br>
I vote for him to be removed as moderator and returned to member status. A more temperate and friendly person should be made moderator in his stead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uyales.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 698<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/31/02 9:11:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yales/images/53invad2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Should Yales be removed as Moderator?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> if Yales didn't keep putting across the myth he was speaking on behalf of the board.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Where?<br>
